<subSubSection pageId="266" pageNumber="871" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="266.[1397,2605,2263,3085]" pageId="266" pageNumber="871">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1397,1633,2736,2770]" pageId="266" pageNumber="871">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
Christina’s Margareta Rat is believed to be nocturnal because holotype was trapped at night. That single rat was captured on Pegunungan Mekongga with the Common Hill Rat (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hoffmann" baseAuthorityYear="1887" box="[1788,2078,2818,2847]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Bunomys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="266" pageNumber="871" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chrysocomus">Bunomys chrysocomus</taxonomicName>
), Montane Hill Rat (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Miller &amp; Hollister" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[2362,2587,2818,2847]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Bunomys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="266" pageNumber="871" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="penitus">Bunomys penitus</taxonomicName>
), Giant Sulawesi Rat (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[1678,1961,2858,2887]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Paruromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="266" pageNumber="871" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dominator">Paruromys dominator</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[1986,2148,2858,2887]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Maxomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="266" pageNumber="871" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="undetermined">Maxomys sp.</taxonomicName>
(undescribed), and the endemic squirrel, the Secretive Dwarf Squirrel (Prosciurillus abstrusus).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
